              }}></path></svg></span>{`Retention Period`}</h5></div><div parentName="div" {...{
        "className": "admonition-content"
      }}><p parentName="div">{`If you want to save the database backups for more than seven days, change the `}<strong parentName="p">{`retentionPeriod`}</strong>{` value.`}</p></div></div>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "create-a-backup"
    }}>{`Create a Backup`}</h3>
    <p>{`To make a backup of all `}<strong parentName="p">{`Databases`}</strong>{` or a specific `}<strong parentName="p">{`Database`}</strong>{`, first login via `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "users#ssh-login"
      }}>{`SSH`}</a>{`.`}</p>
    <p>{`The `}<strong parentName="p">{`Database Backups`}</strong>{` can be found in the directory: `}<strong parentName="p">{`/home/cloudpanel/backups/$databaseName/`}</strong></p>
    <p>{`To backup all `}<strong parentName="p">{`Databases`}</strong>{`, run the following command:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`clpctl db:backup --databases=all
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`The `}<strong parentName="p">{`Output`}</strong>{` will look like:`}</p>
    <img class="border" src={useBaseUrl('img/v1/databases/create_database_backup.png')} /> <br /> <br />
    <p>{`To backup a specific `}<strong parentName="p">{`Database`}</strong>{`, run the following command:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`clpctl db:backup --databases=$databaseName
`}</code></pre>
