          }}>{`mysqldump`}</a>{` from `}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "https://www.mysql.com/"
          }}>{`MySQL`}</a>{`.`}</p></div></div>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "restore-a-backup"
    }}>{`Restore a Backup`}</h3>
    <p>{`For restoring a `}<strong parentName="p">{`Database Backup`}</strong>{`, you can use the `}<strong parentName="p">{`CloudPanel CLI`}</strong>{` or the `}<strong parentName="p">{`mysql`}</strong>{` command:`}</p>
    <h4 {...{
      "id": "restore-via-cloudpanel-cli"
    }}>{`Restore via CloudPanel CLI`}</h4>
    <p>{`1) Login via `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "users#ssh-login"
      }}>{`SSH`}</a>{` to your server.`}</p>
    <p>{`2) Go to the directory where your `}<strong parentName="p">{`Database Dump`}</strong>{` is e.g.:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`cd /home/cloudpanel/backups/wordpress/YYYY-mm-dd/
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`3) Run the following command to restore the `}<strong parentName="p">{`Database Dump`}</strong>{`:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`clpctl db:import --file=dump.sql.gz --database=database-name
`}</code></pre>
    <h4 {...{
      "id": "restore-via-mysql"
    }}>{`Restore via MySQL`}</h4>
    <p>{`The `}<strong parentName="p">{`CloudPanel CLI`}</strong>{` command uses the `}<strong parentName="p">{`mysql`}</strong>{` command for restoring the database under the hood.`}</p>
    <p>{`To restore a `}<strong parentName="p">{`Database Dump`}</strong>{` via normal `}<strong parentName="p">{`mysql`}</strong>{` command, do the following:`}</p>
    <p>{`1) Login via `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "users#ssh-login"
      }}>{`SSH`}</a>{` to your server and become `}<strong parentName="p">{`root`}</strong>{`.`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`sudo su root
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`2) Get the `}<strong parentName="p">{`Master Database Credentials`}</strong>{` with the following command:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`clpctl db:show:credentials
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`The `}<strong parentName="p">{`Output`}</strong>{` will look like:`}</p>
    <img class="border" src={useBaseUrl('img/v1/databases/show_database_credentials.png')} /> <br /> <br />
    <p>{`3) Run the `}<strong parentName="p">{`mysql`}</strong>{` command to restore a gzipped `}<strong parentName="p">{`Database Dump`}</strong>{`.`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`gunzip < dump.sql.gz | mysql -h'127.0.0.1' -P'3306' -u'root' -p'rGLEUUy6o2Wa7eBN' database-name
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`A non-gzipped `}<strong parentName="p">{`Database Dump`}</strong>{` can be imported with the following command:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`mysql -h'127.0.0.1' -P'3306' -u'root' -p'rGLEUUy6o2Wa7eBN' database-name < dump.sql
`}</code></pre>
    <div {...{
