              }}></path></svg></span>{`Warning`}</h5></div><div parentName="div" {...{
        "className": "admonition-content"
      }}><p parentName="div">{`Do not use `}<strong parentName="p">{`phpMyAdmin`}</strong>{` for exporting and importing a database, it can damage your database. `}<br />{`
Use `}<strong parentName="p">{`mysqldump`}</strong>{` for exporting a database and the `}<strong parentName="p">{`mysql`}</strong>{` command for import.`}</p></div></div>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "download-a-backup"
    }}>{`Download a Backup`}</h3>
    <p>{`All database backups can be found in the following directory: `}<strong parentName="p">{`/home/cloudpanel/backups/`}</strong></p>
    <p>{`You can download a single `}<strong parentName="p">{`Database Backup`}</strong>{` via `}<strong parentName="p">{`SCP`}</strong>{`, `}<strong parentName="p">{`rsync`}</strong>{`, or via `}<strong parentName="p">{`CloudPanel`}</strong>{`.`}</p>
    <p>{`To `}<strong parentName="p">{`download`}</strong>{` a backup via `}<strong parentName="p">{`CloudPanel`}</strong>{`, click on the `}<strong parentName="p">{`database`}</strong>{` and on then the tab `}<strong parentName="p">{`Backups`}</strong>{`.`}</p>
    <p>{`Click on the button `}<strong parentName="p">{`Download`}</strong>{` to start the download process.`}</p>
    <img class="border" src={useBaseUrl('img/v1/databases/download_a_backup.png')} />
    </MDXLayout>;
}

